name: Retiring Pilot - Air Canada 767-375ER [C-GSCA] Landing at Calgary Airport ᴴᴰ
description:
Follow me on Flickr: https://www.flickr.com/photos/dude847...

AC10 from Tokyo-Narita to Calgary International Airport today was the final flight of an Air Canada pilot before his retirement. C-GSCA is seen here touching down on 35L, with some kudos from the tower and ground controllers. A water salute was rumored, but the temperature was just above freezing so I assume they called it off. Enjoy this quick upload.

Thanks for watching!
